8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 461, L.D. 722, “An Act to Fund an
10 Administrative Structure of an Emergency Medical Services Education Program in the
11 Community College System”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, Directing the Department of Public Safety, Emergency Medical Services'
14 Board to Report to the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs
15 on the Status of Funds in the Emergency Medical Services Stabilization and
16 Sustainability Program'
17 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
18 'Sec. 1. Department of Public Safety, Emergency Medical Services' Board
19 to report to the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs
20 on program grant funding. Resolved: That the Department of Public Safety,
21 Emergency Medical Services' Board shall report to the Joint Standing Committee on
22 Education and Cultural Affairs on the status of funds in the Emergency Medical Services
23 Stabilization and Sustainability Program, as established by the Maine Revised Statutes,
24 Title 32, section 98, no later than January 15, 2026. The report must include the amount
25 of funding received by emergency medical services training centers in the Maine
26 Community College System and the status of any remaining funds not yet awarded to
27 emergency medical services training centers. The joint standing committee may report out
28 a bill to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature related to the contents of the
29 report.'
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. The resolve directs the Department
3344 of Public Safety, Emergency Medical Services' Board to report to the Joint Standing
3355 Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs on the status of funds in the Emergency
